<p>
<ref type="text" xml:id="r01" target="#q01">These poem notes</ref> may relate to <ref type="work" xml:id="r2" target="#http://www.whitmanarchive.org/works/xxx.00175">"Beat! Beat! Drums!"</ref> which first appeared in <hi rend="italic">Drum-Taps</hi> <date when="1865">(1865)</date>.<!-- [1865: "Beat! Beat! Drums!"(<hi rend="italic">Drum-Taps</hi>). 1867: (early copies of this edition include unbound copies of <hi rend="italic">Drum-Taps</hi>). 1871: "Beat! Beat! Drums!" ("Drum-Taps" cluster).]-->
</p>
</work>
</relations>



<ab><add place="supralinear" rend="unmarked">the</add> long &amp; glittering, <add place="supralinear" rend="unmarked">wide</add>  ranks <del rend="overstrike">they c</del>—will they never stop?—For two whol<subst><del rend="overwrite" seq="1">d</del><add rend="overwrite" place="over" seq="2">e</add></subst> days commencing early in the morning &amp; continuing long into the night—<del rend="overstrike">the</del> the b<subst><del rend="overwrite" seq="1">el</del><add rend="overwrite" place="over" seq="2">ea</add></subst>ting drum<ref xml:id="q01" target="xxx.00175.xml"/>—every musket bright, with <subst><del rend="overwrite" seq="1">s</del><add rend="overwrite" place="over" seq="2">u</add></subst>p–pointed slanting bayonet glinting in the bright sun—</ab>

<milestone unit="undeclared" rend="horbar-short-left"/>

<p>the drums, <subst><del rend="overwrite" seq="1"><gap reason="illegible" extent="one letter" quantity="1" unit="chars"/></del><add rend="overwrite" place="over" seq="2">e</add></subst>ndless drums producing a strange delicious trembling shock in the belly</p>

</div1>

<pb xml:id="leaf009v" facs="uva.00062.013.jpg" type="verso"/>

